        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 4 at 9:50PM CDT until April 4 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 950 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Vandervoort, or
16 miles southwest of Mena, moving north at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Hatton...                         Wickes...
Cove...                           Hatfield...
Mccauley...                       Bogg Springs...
Vandervoort...
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
